Southampton have made an offer for Sporting Lisbon defender Marcos Rojo.

The 24-year-old, who can play at centre back or left-back, started all but one game for Argentina during their run to the World Cup Final in Brazil.

Meanwhile, the club also maintain an interest in Norwich's Nathan Redmond.

Target: Southampton have made an offer for Sporting Lisbon and Argentina defender Marcos Rojo

Linked: They are also interested in Norwich winger Nathan Redmond

Outgoing: Dani Osvaldo is close to a move to Inter Milan

The winger has been linked with a host of Premier League clubs this summer following the Canaries relegation.

Southampton are also close to an agreement with Inter Milan over a deal for Dani Osvaldo, who will become the sixth man to leave St Mary's this summer following Rickie Lambert, Adam Lallana, Luke Shaw, Dejan Lovren and Calum Chambers.

In return, Inter's Algerian midfielder Sapher Taider could join on loan.

